    "body": "It is correct. It tells you to change `x**y**z` to `(x**y)**z` to preserve the old behavior. If you don't do that, it will be interpreted as `x**(y**z)`, changing the meaning of your code, which most likely was written with the assumption that it means `(x**y)**z`.",
